1. docker --version — verify Docker is installed.

2. docker pull nginx — download an image from a registry.

3. docker images — list local images.

4. docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name my-nginx nginx — start an Nginx container in the background.

5. docker ps — view running containers.

6. docker logs my-nginx — inspect a container’s logs.

7. docker exec -it my-nginx /bin/sh — open a shell inside the container.

8. docker stop my-nginx and docker rm my-nginx — stop and remove the container.
